-- Cameroon’s Average Cocoa Exports Rose 2.6% in Week to July 2
-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 2012-07-03T13:50:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/cameroon-s-average-cocoa-exports-rose-2-6-in-week-to-july-2.html
The cocoa export price from
Cameroon’s main port of Douala rose by 2.6 percent, or 30 CFA
francs (6 cents), to 1,182 CFA francs a kilogram (2.2 pounds)
during the week to yesterday, according to a Bloomberg
calculation based on data from the country’s Cocoa and Coffee
Board, sent through mobile-phone text message.  A total of 167,272 metric tons has been exported since the
start of the season, compared with 188,304 tons shipped in the
previous year, the board said on June 26.  The following is a table of exports rates (Free on Board)
at the port in CFA francs per kilogram.  
